Former soldiers who served at the notorious Deepcut barracks speak about life there. We follow their fight for the truth and investigations of what's happened to a dossier of sexual abuse and bullying allegations involving other recruits, which campaigners say should be re-examined. 

	---------------------------------------------

Deepcut.s01e01.A.Familys.Fight.For.The.Truth

For two decades, the army said the death of Welsh soldier Cheryl James at the notorious Deepcut army barracks was suicide. On the eve of the verdict at the new inquest into her death, we exclusively follow her parents Des and Doreen's fight for the truth.
	
	---------------------------------------------

Deepcut.s01e02.The.Armys.Shame

As the inquest into the death of young soldier Cheryl James delivers its verdict, former soldiers who served alongside her at the notorious Deepcut barracks speak about life there - about a culture of bullying and physical and sexual abuse which has cast a shadow over the army for over two decades
